<p>I've been trying to configure a simple domain directive on my apache2.</p>  <p>www . site.com, https:// www . site.com, https:// site.com and site.com will point to C:\SitePath</p>  <p>sub.site.com, <a href="https://sub.site.com" rel="nofollow">https://sub.site.com</a> will point to C:\SitePath\Subdomain</p>  <p>I've tried everything but it never works properly, the servername porperty simply dont matches the requisition. Any ideas?</p>  <p><strong>Here follows my config:</strong></p>  <pre><code>#maindomain &lt;VirtualHost 111.111.111.111:80&gt;     ServerName site.com     ServerAlias www.site.com     DocumentRoot "E:\subdomain"      &lt;Directory "/"&gt; ... &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; &lt;VirtualHost 111.111.111.111:443&gt;     SSLEngine on     SSLCertificateKeyFile "C:\xampp\apache\conf\ssl\subdomain.key"     SSLCertificateFile "C:\xampp\apache\conf\ssl\subdomain.cert"     ServerName site.com     ServerAlias www.site.com     DocumentRoot "E:\subdomain"      &lt;Directory "/"&gt; ... &lt;/VirtualHost&gt;  #subdomain  &lt;VirtualHost 111.111.111.111:80&gt;     ServerName sub.site.com     DocumentRoot "E:\subdomain"      &lt;Directory "/"&gt; ... &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; &lt;VirtualHost 111.111.111.111:443&gt;     SSLEngine on     SSLCertificateKeyFile "C:\xampp\apache\conf\ssl\subdomain.key"     SSLCertificateFile "C:\xampp\apache\conf\ssl\subdomain.cert"     ServerName sub.site.com     DocumentRoot "E:\subdomain"      &lt;Directory "/"&gt; ... &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; </code></pre>